  "published": "2019-10-15",
  "runtimeMin": 55,
  "format": "Sean and Amanda bring in the Ringer's Donnie Kwok to dig into Parasite's limited-release opening, then run stock up/stock down on Joker and a couple of ugly trailers, remember Robert Forster, and preview the Best International Feature race.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "Parasite",
      "note": "with the Ringer's Donnie Kwok",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Parasite",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Bong Joon-ho's seventh feature, and possibly his best: a poor family cons their way into a wealthy household's employ. Won the Palme d'Or, then posted the best per-screen average of the year on a three-theater opening."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Host",
          "year": 2006,
          "note": "Donnie's pick for what to watch before Parasite: Bong's monster movie, broader and more comedic, but built on the same class satire."
        },
        {
          "title": "Memories of Murder",
          "year": 2003,
          "note": "Bong's breakout in Korea, and Song Kang-ho's second film with him. Donnie rewatched it the night before taping."
        },
        {
          "title": "Snowpiercer",
          "year": 2013,
          "note": "The Chris Evans one: genre wrapped around class and capitalism, a through-line in all of Bong's films."
        },
        {
          "title": "Okja",
          "year": 2017,
          "note": "\"Cute Spielbergian movie and then some other things happen,\" per Amanda."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "Stock Up, Stock Down",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Joker",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Stock up: $7 million shy of $200 million after 11 days, whatever the critical consensus."
        },
        {
          "title": "Dolittle",
          "year": 2020,
          "note": "Stock down: a crew member's Reddit thread alleges one of the all-time production fiascos."
        },
        {
          "title": "Jungle Cruise",
          "year": 2020,
          "note": "Stock down: the new trailer plays like Pirates of the Caribbean 7, not the Disneyland ride."
        },
        {
          "title": "Maleficent: Mistress of Evil",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Gets its own review later in the week."
        },
        {
          "title": "Knives Out",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Amanda's already bought a stack of advance tickets, solo."
        },
        {
          "title": "Jackie Brown",
          "year": 1997,
          "note": "Robert Forster's best-known role, as Max Cherry. Tarantino pulled him out of actor obscurity for it."
        },
        {
          "title": "Medium Cool",
          "year": 1969,
          "note": "Haskell Wexler's film gave Forster his start. Sean's tribute recommendation."
        },
        {
          "title": "El Camino: A Breaking Bad Movie",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Forster's last on-screen role, which premiered the same weekend he died."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The Big Race: Best International Feature Film",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Parasite",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "South Korea's submission. \"If it's not nominated, we riot.\""
        },
        {
          "title": "Pain and Glory",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Pedro Almodóvar's autofictional latest. The only other film with comparable buzz outside the Academy."
        },
        {
          "title": "Les Misérables",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "France's submission over Portrait of a Lady on Fire, not the musical."
        },
        {
          "title": "Portrait of a Lady on Fire",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Passed over by France for Les Misérables, flagged as a controversial call once the race heats up."
        },
        {
          "title": "Atlantics",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Senegal's submission, a Netflix acquisition and one of the year's best-reviewed films. Unseen by either host at taping."
        },
        {
          "title": "Weathering With You",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "Japan's submission, from the director of Your Name. Animated films are newly eligible in this category."
        },
        {
          "title": "Honeyland",
